    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27a.36"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Neihardt Collection</note>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">36</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>May 20, 1959</dateline>
                    
                    <address>                
                        <addrLine>Dr. John Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>University of Missouri</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Mo.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>After my conversation with you earlier this year, I sent a story about you and the Indian prayer garden to Together magazine. They wish to use it in their Unusual Methodists department of the magazine. Two things are necessary before they will accept the story. I wonder if you might help me out with them. One is the name of the Methodist church that you attend or have a membership in. I know that your religion is more universal than this, but it's a red tape thing that they consider necessary. Even if you haven't attended the chuch for the last 10 years, it doesn't matter, just so you have the name so I may send it to them. The other thing is a photo of you in the prayer garden, a snapshot if you have one on hand, or possibly the department of information services at the university might have one or would take one for us.</p>
                
                <p>My husband is being transferred back to Chicago and we are in the midst of moving now. I would certainly appreciate it greatly if you could help me out with these two requests so that we could have the editors satisfied before I leave town.</p>
                
                <p>Thank you very much.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Shirley Linde</signed>
                    <signed>Shirley Motter Linde</signed>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine><hi rend="caps">R</hi>-96 Lake Lotawana</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Lee's Summit, Mo.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Mrs. Linde:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I grew up in a Methodist family, but for years I have not attended the Methodist Church. I have, however, talked in Methodist Churches, and I still revere the Church.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute> <signed>John Neihardt</signed>
                    
                    <dateline>6-2-'59</dateline>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
